        },
        {
          "body": "Si Wong Desert",
          "key": "${link_1}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Si_Wong_Desert",
            "page": "Si_Wong_Desert"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "tribe of sandbenders",
          "key": "${link_2}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Sandbender_Tribes",
            "page": "Sandbender_Tribes"
          }
        }
      ],
      "text": "Sha-Mo was a sandbender who spent his life in the Si Wong Desert and thus a master of survival in its harsh environment. He was a man of importance in his tribe of sandbenders."
    },
    {
      "body": "Sha-Mo had a son named ${link_0} with his wife Yulduz, who had died of skin cancer, a common affliction in the sun-drenched Si Wong Desert, leaving him to raise his son on his own.",
      "links": [
        {
          "body": "Ghashiun",
          "key": "${link_0}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Ghashiun",
            "page": "Ghashiun"
          }
        }
      ],
      "text": "Sha-Mo had a son named Ghashiun with his wife Yulduz, who had died of skin cancer, a common affliction in the sun-drenched Si Wong Desert, leaving him to raise his son on his own."
    },
    {
      "body": "Sha-Mo encountered ${link_0} at the ${link_1}, where he and the rest of his tribe saved them from the attacking ${link_2}. He harshly inquired about what they were doing in their land with a ${link_3} stolen from the Hami tribe. His attitude softened a bit upon learning that ${link_4} was the ${link_5} and that they had not stolen the sailer. When his son aggressively accused Team Avatar of believing the sandbenders to be thieves, Sha-Mo quickly demanded his son to be silent, as they had not been accused of anything. He gave Team Avatar the benefit of the doubt, even offering them hospitality under the condition that what they were saying was the truth.",
      "links": [
        {
          "body": "Team Avatar",
          "key": "${link_0}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Team_Avatar",
            "page": "Team_Avatar"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "Si Wong Rock",
          "key": "${link_1}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Si_Wong_Desert#Si_Wong_Rock",
            "page": "Si_Wong_Desert"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "buzzard wasps",
          "key": "${link_2}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Buzzard_wasp",
            "page": "Buzzard_wasp"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "sand-sailer",
          "key": "${link_3}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Sand-sailer",
            "page": "Sand-sailer"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "Aang",
          "key": "${link_4}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Aang",
            "page": "Aang"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "Avatar",
          "key": "${link_5}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Avatar",
            "page": "Avatar"
          }
        }
      ],
      "text": "Sha-Mo encountered Team Avatar at the Si Wong Rock, where he and the rest of his tribe saved them from the attacking buzzard wasps. He harshly inquired about what they were doing in their land with a sand-sailer stolen from the Hami tribe. His attitude softened a bit upon learning that Aang was the Avatar and that they had not stolen the sailer. When his son aggressively accused Team Avatar of believing the sandbenders to be thieves, Sha-Mo quickly demanded his son to be silent, as they had not been accused of anything. He gave Team Avatar the benefit of the doubt, even offering them hospitality under the condition that what they were saying was the truth."
    },
    {
      "body": "When Sha-Mo learned that his son had been responsible for the theft of the Avatar's ${link_0}, he became angry with Ghashiun. Just like the other sandbenders, Sha-Mo cowered back in fear when an enraged Aang entered the ${link_1} and destroyed the remaining sand-sailers, and upon Sokka's urging, he ran away to safety.",
      "links": [
        {
          "body": "bison",
          "key": "${link_0}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Flying_bison",
            "page": "Flying_bison"
          }
        },
        {
          "body": "Avatar State",
          "key": "${link_1}",
          "target": {
            "href": "Avatar#Avatar_State",
            "page": "Avatar"
          }
        }
      ],
      "text": "When Sha-Mo learned that his son had been responsible for the theft of the Avatar's bison, he became angry with Ghashiun. Just like the other sandbenders, Sha-Mo cowered back in fear when an enraged Aang entered the Avatar State and destroyed the remaining sand-sailers, and upon Sokka's urging, he ran away to safety."
    },
    {
      "body": "A hard, grizzled man of few words, Sha-Mo was proud of his sandbender heritage and thus quick to anger when faced with the preconceptions that outsiders often had about sandbenders, such as them being thieves and bandits that preyed on anyone traveling through the desert. Regardless, he was still courteous to outsiders, granting them the benefit of the doubt and willing to give them hospitality.",
      "links": [],
      "text": "A hard, grizzled man of few words, Sha-Mo was proud of his sandbender heritage and thus quick to anger when faced with the preconceptions that outsiders often had about sandbenders, such as them being thieves and bandits that preyed on anyone traveling through the desert. Regardless, he was still courteous to outsiders, granting them the benefit of the doubt and willing to give them hospitality."
    }
